why do countries limit exposure to the world market? There are a few reasons why countries limit exposure to the world market. One reason is to protect their own industries. If a country opens up its markets to too much competition, its own industries may not be able to compete and may go out of business. Another reason is to protect their citizens. If a country opens up its markets to too many imports, the prices of goods may go up and the citizens may not be able to afford them.

why do countries limit exposure to the world market? There can be a number of reasons why a country might limit its exposure to the world market. One reason might be to protect its domestic industries from foreign competition. Another reason might be to keep its currency from becoming too weak or too strong relative to other currencies.
